8. O-O-O Bd7 ( { There are many options here, though nowadays at the highest level only } 8...Bd7 { and sometimes } ) ( 8...Be7 { is seen. Understandably, since the other moves are hated by the engines. } ) { This is the ultimate mainline of the Classical Sicilian Rauzer. There are many games here, old, new, top level, amateurs, everything. White generally has two different directions here. One is to go for f4 which usually leads to Bxf6 gxf6 structures down the road and another is to play a move like 9. f3 (or the modern 9. Kb1!?) and play the Scheveningen style position, resembling the English Attack in the e6 Najdorf. I propose the second path, but with a wrinkle, starting with 9. Kb1!? first. } 
