I should also mention @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/1p1b1ppp/p1nppn2/6B1/3NP3/2N5/PPPQ1PPP/2KR1B1R w kq - 2 9@@EndFEN@@ 9.Nxc6!? Bxc6 10.f3 played by Nepo, which can either transpose to my recommendation after 10...Be7 , or lead to a very safe endgame after 10...h6! 11.Bf4 d5 12.Qe1 Bb4 13.a3 Bxc3 14.Qxc3 O-O 15.Be5 Rc8 16.Bxf6 Qxf6 17.Qxf6 gxf6 18.exd5 Bxd5 19.Rd4 . Nepo used this line to get a safe position against Rapport in the Candidates, when in a must-draw situation, but it's hard to get something going in that endgame with White against a good defense, so I chose not to recommend it for the ambitious players out there. } ) Be7 { The most common and the most natural too, but already quite inaccurate. } 
10. Nxc6!? ( { This is the new trend, to try and take on c6. Doing it a move ago allowed a simplifying sequence as we saw in Nepo-Rapport (where Nepo allowed it on purpose), but on this move, it is much more challenging. Waiting one more move with } 10.f3 { allows } 10...Nxd4 { with a lot of theory, where Black isn't in too bad a shape. } ) Bxc6 
11. f3 { This is a pretty important position for the entire Rauzer. One that Black could avoid (by 9... Nxd4!?), but one that most of the players still don't.

There are a lot of options and move orders. The plans with short castle and b5 are the most common, but not very good since we easily diffuse Black's queenside play with a Ne2-Nd4 maneuver and follow it up without a kingside pawns push. Probably the best attempts to equalize are connected with a d5 push of some sort, but they don't seem all too appealing either. } b5 { Common, but not very much liked by the engine. } 
12. h4 Qc7 ( { MVL combined all the plans against me and got into trouble fast. } 12...O-O { see 11... O-O move order. [/variation/24987977] } ) 
13. Ne2 h6 
14. Be3 d5 
15. e5! { Again, the thematic idea that is key. } Nd7 
16. f4 { I managed to get a dream here. Black shouldn't combine b5 and d5. } Nc5 
17. Nd4 Ne4 
18. Qe1 Bd7 
19. g4 -- ( { Now no matter where Black castles the king is in great danger. MVL went for } 19...O-O-O { , but was strategically lost after } 20.Bd3 { . It was one of the games [/variation/25922268] that I managed to convert against him. } )
