6. g4 { Since Black already committed the knight to c6, it is also possible to explore 6. Be3 setups, but I want to stay consistent and go for g4 here as well, as in the pure Scheveningen. } Be7 {[%csl Rg8]} { Andreikin played this many times in blitz. It is very confusing, but not very good, since the g8 knight eventually anyway needs to land on f6. } ( 6...h6 { The top choice of the engines, which is likely to transpose to a line from the pure Scheveningen. } 7.Be3 Nf6 8.Rg1 { See the Scheveningen with @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pp3ppp/2npp3/8/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@ 6.g4 h6 7.Rg1 .

