17. g4 {[%csl Ge4,Re5,Gf3,Rf7,Gg4,Rg5,Gh5,Rh6]} { Black's position is a strategic disaster. The queenside weaknesses are still there, and the majority on the kingside is totally dead, the knight on e4 stands there forever and so the bishop on g7 is dead forever as well. Why people were allowing this, is beyond me. } Qc7 
18. Bc4 { We just finish development. } Red8 
19. Qf2 { The queen steps out of the x-ray. } Nf4 { This is another bad move, but the way they used to play here. } 
20. Bxe6 Nxe6 
21. Bd6 Qa5 
22. Kb1 {[%cal Gd1d2,Gh1d1,Gc2c3,Gf2f1,Gf1c4][%csl Ge4,Rg7]} { We have a dominant e4 knight and Black is left with the sad bishop on g7. The rest is already conversion, we will double on the d-file and think of retouring the queen with Qf1-Qc4. } *

