3. d4 cxd4 
4. Nxd4 g6 { We can also get this position via @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 g6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nc6 move order. In both cases, white could have avoided it, with a Rossolimo against 2... Nc6 - 3. Bb5, and with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 g6 and now for example 3.c3 or 3.d4 cxd4 4.Qxd4!? . That said, we are happy to get it and embrace the Maroczy bind setup. } 
