17. Qxd2 Qa5 ( { The maneuvre to c5 is pretty, but according to the computer, it might not be the best. The engine prefers } 17...a5 { , when after } 18.c3 bxc3 19.bxc3 Ne7 20.Ne3 { we keep the slightest of the pressures, thanks to Black's vulnerable d6-pawn and a weakened b5-square. } ) 
18. Qd3 ( { In the game I went for } 18.c3 { , which was enough for a mini plus, though then a lot of ups and downs happened in the game, before it was eventually drawn. Stronger, however, is to start with } ) ( 18.Qd3 { . } ) Qc5 
19. Rfd1 f5 ( { The key here is that the tempting } 19...f5 { is met with } 20.Ne3! { when Black has serious issues with the soft d6 pawn. } ) 
20. Ne3 Bxc4 
21. Qxc4 { The endgames are good for White. } *

