[ECO "B29"]

1. e4 c5 
2. Nf3 Nf6 { This system is very dubious, but it's reasonably popular on the amateur and club level and even some strong Grandmasters occasionally use it, in the hope to catch the opponent off guard. It does have the advantage of engaging with our e4 pawn right away, creating complications quickly. } 
3. e5 {[%mdl 32768]} ( { White can also try to transpose to the standard open Sicilian with } 3.Nc3 { , when Black can try } 3...d5 { , to stay true to their dubious intentions. That said, I feel we should exploit Black's mistake on move 2 and not give any second chances to get back into a normal opening. } ) Nd5 ( { This is Black's only reply, if } 3...Ng4 4.h3 { knight gets kicked away. } ) 
4. Nc3 Nxc3 
5. dxc3 { Black had a setup with Nc6, e6, Qc7, b6, Bb7 O-O-O and so on, but having spent too much time with the knight, they won't be in time to get everything done undisturbed. } Nc6 
6. Bf4 Qb6 
7. Bd3! ( { This is a very optimistic move. Black is seriously thinking that attacking our b2 pawn will lead to us weakening our queenside with } 7.b3 { , but that's obviously not happening. } ) { It is quite obvious that this is a good idea, Black is so much behind in development and yet not many people dared sacrifice the pawns. } Qxb2 
8. O-O {[%cal Gf1e1,Gd3e4]} { Our compensation is reasonably abstract here, in a sense that we don't win by force, but by just improving our pieces, we will slowly get Black cornered. } e6 { This is a sample line, Black tries to finish the development. } 
9. Be4 {[%cal Gd1d3]} { Improving the bishop and also intending Qd3. } Qxc3 { Black can grab one more, we don't mind. } 
10. Re1 Be7 
11. a4 { We are not in rush, but slowly taking the squares away from the Black queen. } Qa5 { The queen runs away to safety, but now we can regroup before going into the decisive offensive. } 
12. Nd2 {[%cal Gd2c4,Gd1g4,Ga1a3]} { The knight is chasing the queen and heads towards d6, while the queen's diagonal is open to jump towards g4 and another reason for the a2-a4! move revealed - the rook lift is incoming with Ra3. Black is in trouble here. } *

