6. Bf4 e6 { The most often played move, but it's not great it seems. Perhaps Black should delay weakening the d6 square instead. } 
7. Nd2! {[%mdl 32768]} {[%csl Rd6]} { I was surprised to see that this move has barely been played still, even though the computer shouts it from a mile away. We are going for the weak d6 square and after Black's forced d5/d6 break, we will use our better development to get a tangible advantage. } d5 ( { This or } 7...d6 { is forced since otherwise, Ne4 will get a grip on the hopelessly weak d6-square. } ) 
8. exd6 Bxd6 
9. Qf3 {[%cal Ge1c1,Gd2e4]} { Very harmonious, we defend the f4 bishop and prepare a quick long castle. } O-O 
10. O-O-O Bxf4 
