14. Qc4 ( { White has a few options here. The best are } 14.Qc4!? { and } ) ( 14.c3 { , because the simplest } ) ( 14.Bd3 { might be too little. } ) { Practically, I believe this to be the best. The queen is helping us develop the queenside without making concessions like Bd3 Bxd3 cxd3. } Rac8 { This is the most natural move to me and also the only one that has been played. It doesn't work well though. } 
15. c3! {[%mdl 32768]} { We have to diffuse the Nb4 threat and it turns out Black doesn't have any really good discoveries. } Nb4 
16. Be3 ( { Also } 16.Qd4! Nc2 17.Qxb6 axb6 18.Nd4! { is a full pawn in the end. } ) Rxc4 
17. Bxb6 Bd3 { Now we have a precise sequence to just keep the full pawn. } 
18. Bxd3 Nxd3 
19. b3! { Accurate. } Rxc3 
20. Bxa7 { Black has no compensation here for the pawn, it's just a struggle now. } *

