6. f3 e5 ( { This is how Black plays. Some go for } 6...Nc6 { followed by g6, but that would be a dubious version of the Dragon, as we follow with the Yugoslav Attack setup, with Be3 Qd2 and O-O-O. } ) 
7. Nb3 Be7 
8. Be3 O-O 
9. Qd2 a5 { This is the system they play here. The idea is to play this extremely dubious a5 variation of the Najdorf and hope that the opponent is not familiar with the English Attack. True, since we play 6. h3 against the Najdorf, we aren't, but we will cover this particular line, so basically we will be. } 
